obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (20991)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20991&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Warehousing`
  line `Corporations Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1* * *.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 37 of 1989, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-10-1989).`
  line
  line `2. 18th March, 1963; vide notification No. G.S.R. 463, dated 16th March, 1963, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Pt. II,`
  line `sec. 3 (i).`
  line
  line `This Act shall, in its application to the States specified in the Schedule to Act 20 of 1965, have effect as if in`
  line `clause (e) of section 2 the words and figures "being a commodity with respect to which Parliament has power to make`
  line `laws by virtue of entry 33 in List III in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution" had been omitted: vide Act 20 of 1965, s.`
  line `2 (w.e.f. 27-11-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (20992)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20992&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "agricultural produce" means any of the following classes of commodities, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) foodstuffs, including edible oil-seeds;`
  line
  line `(ii) cattle fodder, including oil-cakes and other concentrates;`
  line
  line `(iii) raw cotton, whether ginned or unginned, and cotton seed;`
  line
  line `(iv) raw jute; and`
  line
  line `(v) vegetable oils;`
  line
  line `(b) "appropriate Government" means in relation to the Central Warehousing Corporation, the`
  line `Central Government, and in relation to a State Warehousing Corporation, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(c) "Central Warehousing Corporation" means the Central Warehousing Corporation`
  line `established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "co-operative society" means a society registered or deemed to be registered under the Cooperative`
  line `Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912), or under any other law with respect to co-operative`
  line `societies for the time being in force in any State, which is engaged in the processing, marketing,`
  line `storage, export or import of agricultural produce or any notified commodity or in insurance`
  line `business and includes a co-operative land mortgage bank;`
  line
  line `^1[(dd) "nationalised bank" means a corresponding new bank specified in the First Schedule to`
  line `the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970); ^2[or a`
  line `corresponding new bank specified in the First Schedule to the Banking Companies (Acquisition`
  line `and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980).]`
  line
  line `(e) "notified commodity" means any commodity (other than agricultural produce) which the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a notified`
  line `commodity for the purposes of this Act, being a commodity with respect to which Parliament has`
  line `power to make laws by virtue of entry 33 in List III in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "recognised association" means an association which is for the time being recognised by`
  line `the Central Government under section 6 of the Forward Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1952 (74 of`
  line `1952);`
  line
  line `(h) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(i) "scheduled bank" means a bank for the time being included in the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) ^3[, and includes a nationalised bank];`
  line
  line `(j) "State Bank" means the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India Act,`
  line `1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(k) "State Warehousing Corporation" means a Warehousing Corporation for a State`
  line `established or deemed to be established under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Warehousing Corporation" means a Warehousing Corporation established or deemed to`
  line `be established under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(m) "year" means the financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 37 of 1989, s. 3 (w.e.f. 22-10-1989).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (20993)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Construction of references to any law not in force or any functionary not in existence in any State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 37 of 1989, s. 4 (w.e.f. 22-10-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20993&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Construction of references to any law not in force or any functionary not in existence`
  line `in any State.--Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force, or any functionary not in`
  line `existence, in any State, shall, in relation to that State, be construed as a reference to the corresponding`
  line `law in force, or the corresponding functionary in existence, in that State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (20994)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `The Central Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 34 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-9-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20994&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf, the Central`
  line `Government shall establish a Corporation by the name of the Central Warehousing Corporation which`
  line `shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal with power to acquire, hold`
  line `and dispose of property and to contract, and may, by the said name, sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(2) The head-office of the Central Warehousing Corporation shall be at New Delhi ^1[or at such`
  line `other place as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify].`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (20995)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Share capital and shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20995&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authorised share capital of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation shall be twenty crores of rupees divided into two hundred thousand shares`
  line `of the face value of one thousand rupees each; any shares remaining to be issued may be issued, with`
  line `the sanction of the Central Government from time to time, as and when the Central Warehousing`
  line `Corporation may deem fit:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Central Government may, from time to time, by order notified in the Official`
  line `Gazette, increase the authorised share capital of the Central Warehousing Corporation to such extent`
  line `and in such manner as that Government may determine.]`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[The Central Government shall, after due appropriation made by Parliament by law for the`
  line `purpose,] subscribe for forty per cent. of the share capital issued at any time and the remaining sixty`
  line `per cent. of the share capital may be subscribed for, within such period and in such proportion as may`
  line `be specified by the Central Government, by the following institutions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the State Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) other scheduled banks;`
  line
  line `(c) co-operative societies;`
  line
  line `(d) insurance companies, investment trusts and other financial institutions;`
  line
  line `(e) recognised associations and companies dealing in agricultural produce or any notified`
  line commodity.
  line
  line `(3) If any portion of the sixty per cent. of the share capital referred to in sub-section (2) remains`
  line `unallotted, it may be subscribed for by the Central Government and the State Bank in such proportion`
  line `as may be agreed upon between them and in default of such agreement, as may be determined by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The shares of the Central Warehousing Corporation shall not be transferable except to the`
  line `Central Government, ^3[the State Bank or any other scheduled bank], any insurance company, any`
  line `investment trust or other financial institution or any co-operative society or any recognised association`
  line `or company dealing in agricultural produce or any notified commodity, in accordance with the`
  line `regulations made by the Central Warehousing Corporation under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 3, for "The Central Government shall" (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "the State Bank, any scheduled bank" (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (20996)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Shares to be guaranteed by Central Government and to be trust or approved securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20996&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The shares of the Central Warehousing Corporation shall be guaranteed by the`
  line `Central Government as to the repayment of the principal and the payment of the annual dividend at`
  line `such minimum rate as may be fixed by the Central Government, by notification published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, at the time of the issue of the shares.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Acts mentioned in this sub-section, the shares of`
  line `the Central Warehousing Corporation shall be deemed to be included among the securities`
  line `enumerated in section 20 of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), and also to be approved`
  line `securities for the purpose of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938) and the Banking Companies Act,`
  line `1949 (10 of 1949).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (20997)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Management of Central Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20997&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence and`
  line `management of the affairs and business of the Central Warehousing Corporation shall vest in a board`
  line `of directors who, with the assistance of an Executive Committee and a managing director, may`
  line `exercise all the powers and discharge all the functions which may be exercised or discharged by the`
  line `Central Warehousing Corporation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The board of directors shall act on business principles having regard to public interest and`
  line `shall be guided by such instructions on questions of policy as may be given to them by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) If any doubt arises as to whether a question is or is not a question of policy, the decision of the`
  line `Central Government shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (20998)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title Directors.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20998&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The board of directors referred to in section 6 shall consist of the following,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) six directors to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) one director to be nominated by the State Bank;`
  line
  line `(d) one director to be elected by other scheduled banks;`
  line
  line `(e) one director to be elected by co-operative societies;`
  line
  line `(f) one director to be elected by insurance companies, investment trusts and other financial`
  line `institutions, recognised associations and companies dealing in agricultural produce or notified`
  line commodities;
  line
  line `^2[(ff) three directors to be appointed by the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(g) a managing director, appointed by the Central Government in consultation with the`
  line `directors referred to in clauses (a) to (f):`
  line
  line `Provided that the three directors to be elected under clauses (d), (e) and (f) may, for the first`
  line `constitution of the board of directors, be nominated by the Central Government in such manner as to`
  line `give representation to each class of institutions (whether they have become shareholders of the`
  line `Corporation or not) referred to in those clauses, but a director so nominated shall hold office only`
  line `until he is replaced by a director elected as provided in that clause, and the director so elected shall`
  line `hold office only for so long as the director replaced would have held office had he not been replaced.`
  line
  line `(2) The directors referred to in clauses (d), (e) and (f) of sub-section (1) shall be elected in the`
  line `prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) If, within the period prescribed in this behalf, or within such further period as the Central`
  line `Government may allow, the institutions referred to in clause (d) or clause (e) or clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (1) fail to elect a director, the Central Government may nominate a director to fill the`
  line vacancy.
  line
  line `(4) The board of directors shall have a Chairman ^3*** who shall be appointed by the Central`
  line `Government from among the directors.`
  line
  line `^2[(4A) The directors appointed under clause (ff) of sub-section (1) shall be entitled to receive such`
  line `salary and allowances as the Central Warehousing Corporation may, with the approval of the Central`
  line `Government, determine.]`
  line
  line `(5) The managing director shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise such powers and perform such duties as the board of directors or the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation may entrust or delegate to him; and`
  line
  line `(b) receive such salary and allowances as the Central Warehousing Corporation may, with the`
  line `approval of the Central Government, fix.`
  line
  line `(6) The directors of the Central Warehousing Corporation other than the managing director shall`
  line `be entitled to receive by way of remuneration such sums as the Central Warehousing Corporation`
  line `may, with the approval of the Central Government, fix:`
  line
  line `Provided that no official director shall be entitled to receive any remuneration other than the`
  line `allowances, if any, admissible to him under the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line
  line `(7) The term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, the directors shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (b) omitted by Act 45 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-11-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-11-2005).`
  line
  line `3. The words "and a Vice-Chairman" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-11-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (20999)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Disqualification for office of director of the Central Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 45 of 2005, s. 3, for "the managing director" (w.e.f. 15-11-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=20999&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line A
  line `person shall be disqualified for being chosen as, and for being, a director of the Central Warehousing`
  line Corporation--
  line
  line `(i) if he is found to be a lunatic or becomes of unsound mind; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if he is, or at any time has been, adjudicated insolvent or has suspended payment of his`
  line `debts or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if he is or has been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude and sentenced in`
  line `respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months, unless a period of five years has`
  line `elapsed from the date of expiry of the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(iv) if he has been removed or dismissed from the service of Government or a Corporation`
  line `owned and controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(v) except in the case of ^1[the directors appointed under clause (ff) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 7 and the managing director], if he is a salaried official of the Central Warehousing`
  line `Corporation or any State Warehousing Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(vi) if he is personally interested in any subsisting contract made with, or in any work being`
  line `done for the Central Warehousing Corporation except as a shareholder (other than a director) in`
  line `any public company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956):`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such person is a shareholder, he shall disclose to the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation the nature and extent of shares held by him in such company.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21000)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Removal of directors from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21000&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, at any time in`
  line `consultation with the Central Warehousing Corporation, remove the managing director from office`
  line `after giving him a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed removal.`
  line
  line `(2) The board of directors may remove from office any director who--`
  line
  line `(a) is or has become subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 8; or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the board of directors for more than three consecutive meetings`
  line `of the board without cause sufficient in the opinion of the board, to exonerate his absence.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21001)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appointment of officers, etc., and their conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21001&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation may appoint such officers and other employees as it considers necessary for`
  line `the efficient performance of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person employed by the Central Warehousing Corporation under this Act shall be`
  line `subject to such conditions of service and shall be entitled to such remuneration as may be determined`
  line `by regulations made by the Corporation under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21002)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of Central Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21002&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Central Warehousing Corporation may--`
  line
  line `(a) acquire and build godowns and warehouses at such suitable places in India ^1[ or aboard]`
  line `as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(b) run warehouses for the storage of agricultural produce, seeds, manures, fertilizers,`
  line `agricultural implements and notified commodities offered by individuals, co- operative societies`
  line `and other institutions;`
  line
  line `(c) arrange facilities for the transport of agricultural produce, seeds, manures, fertilizers,`
  line `agricultural implements and notified commodities to and from warehouses;`
  line
  line `(d) subscribe to the share capital of a State Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(e) act as agent of the Government for the purposes of the purchase, sale, storage and`
  line `distribution of agricultural produce, seeds, manures, fertilizers, agricultural implements and`
  line `notified commodities; ^2* * *`
  line
  line `^3[(ea) enter into, with the previous approval of the Central Government, joint ventures with`
  line `any corporation established by or under any Central Act or any State Act or with any company`
  line `formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) including foreign company or`
  line `through its subsidiary companies, for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, the expression "foreign company" shall have`
  line `the meaning assigned to it under clause (23A) of section 2 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of`
  line `1961).`
  line
  line `(eb) establish subsidiary companies; and]`
  line
  line `(f) carry out such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by Act 23 of 2001, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21003)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21003&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an Executive Committee of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation which shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman ^1*** of the board of directors;`
  line
  line `(b) the managing director; and`
  line
  line `(c) two other directors chosen by the Corporation in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Chairman of the board of directors shall be the Chairman of the Executive Committee.]`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general control, direction and superintendence of the board of directors, the`
  line `Executive Committee shall be competent to deal with any matter within the competence of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and the Vice-Chairman" omitted by Act 45 of 2005, s. 4 (w.e.f. 15-11-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-11-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21004)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Meetings of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21004&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The annual general meeting of the Central Warehousing`
  line `Corporation (hereinafter referred to as the annual general meeting) shall be held every year either at`
  line `its head-office or at any other office of the Corporation within six months of the close of the financial`
  line `year, and any other general meeting may be convened by the board of directors at any other time.`
  line
  line `(2) The shareholders present at the annual general meeting shall be entitled to discuss the annual`
  line `accounts, the report of the board of directors on the working of the Corporation during the year under`
  line `report, as well as the auditors' report on the annual balance-sheet and accounts.`
  line
  line `(3) The board of directors of the Central Warehousing Corporation shall, on the requisition of`
  line `one-third of the number of shareholders of the Corporation, call a special meeting of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) The requisition for a special meeting under sub-section (3) shall state the object of the`
  line `meeting, and shall be signed by the requisitionists and deposited at the head-office of the Corporation,`
  line `and may consist of several documents in like form each signed by one or more requisitionists.`
  line
  line `(5) If the board of directors of the Central Warehousing Corporation do not proceed within`
  line `twenty-one days from the date of the requisition being so deposited to cause the special meeting to be`
  line `called, the requisitionists, or a majority of them, may, themselves call the meeting, but in either case,`
  line `the meeting so called shall be held within three months from the date of the deposit of the requisition.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Warehousing Corporation shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the`
  line `transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at meetings) as may be provided by`
  line `regulations made by the Central Warehousing Corporation under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (21005)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Grants and loans by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21005&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after`
  line `due appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Central Warehousing`
  line `Corporation for the purposes of either fund maintained by the Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) by way of grants, such sums of money as the Central Government may consider`
  line `necessary; and`
  line
  line `(b) by way of loans, such sums of money on such terms and conditions as the Central`
  line `Government may determine;`
  line
  line `(2) When making a payment under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall specify the fund`
  line `for the purposes of which the payment is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (21006)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Corporation to maintain two funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21006&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Central Warehousing Corporation shall maintain`
  line `two separate funds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Warehousing Fund (hereinafter referred to as the Warehousing Fund); and`
  line
  line `(b) the General Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (21007)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Warehousing Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 4 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21007&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) To the Warehousing Fund shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys and other securities transferred to the Central Warehousing Corporation under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 43;`
  line
  line `(b) such grants and loans as the Central Government may make for the purposes of the`
  line `Warehousing Fund; and`
  line
  line `(c) such sums of money as may, from time to time, be realised out of the loans made from the`
  line `Warehousing Fund or from interest on loans or dividends on investments made from that fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The Warehousing Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for advancing loans to State Governments on such terms and conditions as the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation may deem fit for the purpose of enabling them to subscribe to the share`
  line `capital of State Warehousing Corporations;`
  line
  line `(b) for advancing loans and granting subsidies to State Warehousing Corporations or to State`
  line `Governments on such terms and conditions as the Central Warehousing Corporation may deem fit`
  line `for the purpose of promoting the warehousing and storage of agricultural produce and notified`
  line `commodities, otherwise than through co-operative societies;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) for meeting the expenses incurred in relation to the training of personnel, or publicity`
  line `and propaganda, for the purpose of promoting warehousing and storage of agricultural produce`
  line `and notified commodities;`
  line
  line `(d) for meeting the expenses, including the salary, allowances and other remuneration of the`
  line `officers and other employees, incurred in relation to the administration of the Warehousing Fund.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (21008)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `General Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1 . The proviso ins. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 5 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21008&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) To the General Fund shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all sums received by the Central Warehousing Corporation other than those referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16; and`
  line
  line `(b) such grants and loans as the Central Government may make for the purposes of the`
  line `General Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The General Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) for meeting the salary, allowances and other remuneration of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Central Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) for meeting the other administrative expenses of the Corporation; and`
  line
  line `(c) for carrying out the purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the General Fund shall not be applied for meeting the expenses referred to in`
  line `clause (c) or clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 16.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (21009)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `State Warehousing Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21009&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette and with the approval of the Central Warehousing Corporation, establish a`
  line `Warehousing Corporation for the State under such name as may be specified in the notification.`
  line `(2) A State Warehousing Corporation established under sub-section (1) shall be a body corporate`
  line `by the name notified under that sub-section, having perpetual succession and a common seal, with`
  line `power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and may, by the said name, sue and be`
  line sued.
  line `(3) The head-office of a State Warehousing Corporation shall be at such place within the State as`
  line `may be notified in the Official Gazette.`
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1), (2) and (3), it shall not be necessary`
  line `for the State Government to establish a Corporation under sub-section (1) where, under clause (g) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 43, a Corporation is deemed to be established for that State under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (21010)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Share capital and shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21010&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authorised capital of a State Warehousing`
  line `Corporation shall be such sum not exceeding two crores of rupees as may be prescribed, divided into`
  line `shares of the face value of one hundred rupees each, of which such number as may be determined by`
  line `the Corporation in consultation with the State Government shall be issued in the first instance and the`
  line `remaining shares may be issued, from time to time, as and when the Corporation may deem fit after`
  line `consultation with the Central Warehousing Corporation and with the sanction of the State`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that in respect of any State Warehousing Corporation the Central Government may,`
  line `after consultation with the State Government concerned, from time to time and by order notified in the`
  line `Official Gazette, increase the maximum limit of the authorised capital aforesaid to such extent and in`
  line `such manner as the Central Government may determine.]`
  line
  line `(2) Of the share capital issued in the first instance and of any subsequent issue of such capital, the`
  line `Central Warehousing Corporation shall, in any case where the State Government has subscribed for`
  line `fifty per cent. of such capital, subscribe for the remaining fifty per cent. of the capital.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (21011)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Management of a State Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2001, s. 3, for "with the previous approval of" (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21011&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence and`
  line `management of the affairs of a State Warehousing Corporation shall vest in a board of directors which`
  line `shall consist of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) five directors nominated by the Central Warehousing Corporation, of whom one shall be`
  line `nominated in consultation with the State Bank and one at least shall be a non-official;`
  line
  line `(b) five directors nominated by the State Government; and`
  line
  line `(c) a managing director, appointed by the State Government in consultation with the directors`
  line `referred to in clauses (a) and (b) and ^1[under intimation to] with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Warehousing Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the board of directors shall be appointed by the State Government from`
  line `among the directors of the State Warehousing Corporation with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The managing director shall--`
  line
  line `(a) exercise such powers and perform such duties as the board of directors or the State`
  line `Warehousing Corporation may entrust or delegate to him; and`
  line
  line `(b) receive such salary and allowances as the State Warehousing Corporation may, in`
  line `consultation with the Central Warehousing Corporation, and with previous approval of the State`
  line `Government, fix.`
  line
  line `(4) The board of directors shall act on business principles having regard to public interest and`
  line `shall be guided by such instructions on questions of policy as may be given to them by the State`
  line `Government or the Central Warehousing Corporation.`
  line
  line `(5) If any doubt arises as to whether a question is or is not a question of policy, or, if the State`
  line `Government and the Central Warehousing Corporation give conflicting instructions, the matter shall`
  line `be referred to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) The directors of a State Warehousing Corporation, other than the managing director, shall be`
  line `entitled to receive by way of remuneration such sums as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no official director shall be entitled to receive any remuneration other than any`
  line `allowances admissible to him under the rules regulating his conditions of service.`
  line
  line `(7) The term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, directors shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (21012)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Disqualification for office of director of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. The words "the Central Warehousing Corporation or" omitted by Act 23 of 2001, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21012&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `A person shall be disqualified`
  line `for being chosen as, and for being, a director of a State Warehousing Corporation--`
  line
  line `(i) if he is found to be a lunatic or becomes of unsound mind; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if he is, or at any time has been, adjudicated insolvent or has suspended payment of his`
  line `debts or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if he is or has been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude and sentenced in`
  line `respect thereof to imprisonment for not less than six months, unless a period of five years has`
  line `elapsed from the date of expiry of the sentence; or`
  line
  line `(iv) if he has been removed or dismissed from service of Government or a corporation owned`
  line `and controlled by the Government; or`
  line
  line `(v) except in the case of the managing director, if he is a salaried official of ^1* * * a State`
  line `Warehousing Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(vi) if he is personally interested in a subsisting contract made with, or in any work being`
  line `done for, the State Warehousing Corporation except as a shareholder (other than a director) in any`
  line `public company as defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956):`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such person is a shareholder, he shall disclose to the Warehousing`
  line `Corporation the nature and extent of the shares held by him in such company.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (21013)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Removal of directors from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "with the previous approval of" (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21013&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, at any time, ^1[under`
  line `intimation to] of the Central Warehousing Corporation, remove the managing director from office`
  line `after giving him a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed removal.`
  line
  line `(2) The board of directors may remove from office any director who--`
  line
  line `(a) is or has become subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 21; or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the board of directors for more than three consecutive meetings`
  line `of the board without cause sufficient, in the opinion of the board, to exonerate his absence.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (21014)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appointment of officers, etc., and their conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21014&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Warehousing`
  line `Corporation may appoint such officers and other employees as it considers necessary for the efficient`
  line `performance of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person employed by a State Warehousing Corporation under this Act shall be subject to`
  line `such conditions of service and shall be entitled to such remuneration as may be determined by`
  line `regulations made by the Corporation under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (21015)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Functions of the State Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21015&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, a`
  line `State Warehousing Corporation may--`
  line
  line `(a) acquire and build godowns and warehouses at such places within the State as it may,`
  line `^1[after consultation with] the Central Warehousing Corporation, determine;`
  line
  line `(b) run warehouses in the State for the storage of agricultural produce, seeds, manures,`
  line `fertilizers, agricultural implements and notified commodities;`
  line
  line `(c) arrange facilities for the transport of agricultural produce, seeds, manures, fertilizers,`
  line `agricultural implements and notified commodities to and from warehouses;`
  line
  line `(d) act as an agent of the Central Warehousing Corporation or of the Government for the`
  line `purposes of the purchase, sale, storage and distribution, of agricultural produce, seeds, manures,`
  line `fertilizers, agricultural implements and notified commodities; ^2* * *`
  line
  line `^3[(da) enter into, with the previous approval of the State Government, joint ventures with the`
  line `Central Warehousing Corporation; and]`
  line
  line `(e) carry out such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2001, s. 6, for "with the previous approval of" (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (21016)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21016&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be an Executive Committee of a State Warehousing`
  line `Corporation which shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman of the board of directors;`
  line
  line `(b) the managing director; and`
  line
  line `(c) three other directors chosen in the prescribed manner, of whom one shall be a director`
  line `referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 20.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the board of directors shall be the Chairman of the Executive Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to any general or special directions as the board of directors may, from time to time,`
  line `give, the Executive Committee shall be competent to deal with any matter within the competence of`
  line `the State Warehousing Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (21017)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Submission of programme of activities and financial estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21017&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Warehousing`
  line `Corporation shall prepare before the commencement of each year a statement of programme of its`
  line `activities during the forthcoming year as well as a financial estimate in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) A statement prepared under sub-section (1) shall, not later than three months before the`
  line `commencement of each year, be submitted for approval--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Central Warehousing Corporation, to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a State Warehousing Corporation, to the Central Warehousing Corporation`
  line `and the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The statement and the financial estimate of a Warehousing Corporation referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) may, with the approval of the Central Government in the case of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation, or with the approval of the Central Warehousing Corporation and the State`
  line `Government in the case of a State Warehousing Corporation, be revised by the Warehousing`
  line Corporation.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (21018)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Borrowing powers of Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21018&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Warehousing Corporation may,`
  line `in consultation with the Reserve Bank and with the previous approval of the appropriate Government,`
  line `issue and sell bonds and debentures carrying interest for the purpose of raising funds:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total amount of bonds and debentures issued and outstanding and of the other`
  line `borrowings of the Corporation shall not at any time exceed ten times the amount of the paid-up share`
  line `capital and the reserve fund of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) A Warehousing Corporation may, for the purpose of carrying out its functions under this Act,`
  line `borrow money--`
  line
  line `(i) from the Reserve Bank, or`
  line
  line `(ii) from the State Bank, for such periods for which, and upon any of the securities against`
  line `which, it is authorised to advance and lend moneys, under the provisions of ^1[the State Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), or]`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) from any ^3[scheduled bank], or`
  line
  line `(iv) from such insurance company, investment trust or other financial institution as may be`
  line `approved by the Central Government in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the proviso to sub-section (1), the Central Warehousing Corporation may borrow`
  line `money from the Central Government and a State Warehousing Corporation may borrow money from`
  line `the State Government and the Central Warehousing Corporation on such securities and on such terms`
  line `and conditions as may be agreed upon between the borrowing Corporation and the lender, in each`
  line case.
  line
  line `(4) The bonds and debentures of a Warehousing Corporation may be guaranteed by the`
  line `appropriate Government as to the repayment of principal and the payment of interest at such rate as`
  line `may be fixed by the appropriate Government on the recommendation of the board of directors of the`
  line `Corporation at the time the bonds or debentures are issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 7, for "the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955)" (w.e.f. 24-3- 1976).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 45 of 2005, s. 5, for "nationalised bank" (w.e.f. 15-11-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (21019)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Deposit account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21019&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `All moneys belonging to a Warehousing Corporation shall be deposited in`
  line `the Reserve Bank or the State Bank ^1[or any nationalised bank] or, subject to any rules made under`
  line `this Act, in ^2[any other scheduled bank] or co-operative bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 8 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "any scheduled bank" (w.e.f. 24-3- 1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (21020)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Investment of funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21020&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `A Warehousing Corporation may invest its funds in the securities of`
  line `the Central or any State Government or in such other manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (21021)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Disposal of profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21021&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Warehousing Corporation shall establish a reserve fund out`
  line `of its annual net profits.`
  line
  line `(2) After making provision for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation on assets and all other matters`
  line `which are usually provided for by companies registered and incorporated under the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), a Warehousing Corporation may, out of its net annual profits, declare a dividend:`
  line
  line `Provided that for so long as the reserve fund is less than the paid-up share capital of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation and until there has been repaid to the Central Government such sum, if any,`
  line `as that Government may have paid under a guarantee given in pursuance of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5 or sub-section (4) of section 27, the rate of such dividend, in the case of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation, shall not exceed the rate guaranteed by the Central Government under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (21022)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Accounts and audit of Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21022&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Warehousing Corporation`
  line `shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts`
  line `including the profit and loss account and the balance sheet in such form as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of the Central Warehousing Corporation, the accounts relating to the`
  line `Warehousing Fund and the General Fund shall be maintained separately.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of a Warehousing Corporation shall be audited by an auditor duly qualified to`
  line `act as an auditor of companies under section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(3) The said auditor shall be appointed by the appropriate Government on the advice of the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(4) The auditor shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance sheet and the profit and loss`
  line `account of the Warehousing Corporation and it shall be his duty to examine them together with the`
  line `accounts and vouchers relating thereto, and he shall have a list delivered to him of all books kept by`
  line `the Corporation and shall at all reasonable times have access to the books, accounts and other`
  line `documents of the Corporation and may require from any officer of the Corporation such information`
  line `and explanations as the auditor may think necessary for the performance of his duties as auditor.`
  line
  line `(5) The auditor shall make a report to the shareholders on the accounts examined by him and on`
  line `the annual balance sheet and the profit and loss account and in every such report, he shall state`
  line `whether in his opinion the accounts give a true and fair view--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the balance sheet, of the state of the Corporation's affairs at the end of its`
  line `financial year, and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of the profit and loss account, of the profit or loss for its financial year,`
  line
  line `and in case he has called for any explanation or information from the officers, whether it has been`
  line `given and whether it is satisfactory.`
  line
  line `(6) The appropriate Government may, after consultation with the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral`
  line `of India at any time issue directions to the auditor requiring him to report to the appropriate`
  line `Government upon the adequacy of measures taken by a Warehousing Corporation for the protection`
  line `of its shareholders and creditors or upon the sufficiency of his procedure in auditing the accounts of`
  line `the Corporation and may enlarge or extend the scope of the audit or direct that a different procedure in`
  line `audit may be adopted or direct that any other examination may be made by the auditor if in the`
  line `opinion of the appropriate Government public interest so requires.`
  line
  line `(7) A Warehousing Corporation shall send a copy of every report of the auditor to the Comptroller`
  line `and Auditor-General of India and to the Central Government at least one month before it is placed`
  line `before the shareholders.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained in this section, the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral`
  line `of India may, either of his own motion or on a request received in this behalf from the`
  line `appropriate Government, undertake in respect of a Warehousing Corporation such audit and at such`
  line `time as he may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Government is required to make any payment on account of the`
  line `guarantee given by it under sub-section (1) of section 5, such audit shall be undertaken by the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any person authorised by him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(9) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person authorised by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of a Warehousing Corporation shall have the same rights,`
  line `privileges and authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `the office of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(10) The annual accounts of a Warehousing Corporation together with the audit report thereon`
  line `shall be placed before the annual general meeting of the Corporation within six months of the close of`
  line `the financial year.`
  line
  line `(11) Every audit report under this section shall be forwarded to the appropriate Government`
  line `within a month of its being placed before the annual general meeting and that Government shall as`
  line `soon thereafter as may be cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament or the`
  line `Legislature of the State, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (21023)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 33
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. ns. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 9 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21023&sectionno=31A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Returns and reports.-- A Warehousing Corporation shall furnish to the appropriate`
  line `Government such returns, statistics, accounts and other information with respect to its property or`
  line `activities as that Government may, from time to time, require.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (21024)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate acts and proceedings of Warehousing Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21024&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of a Warehousing Corporation shall be invalid by reason only`
  line `of the existence of any vacancy among its directors or any defect in the constitution thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (21025)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21025&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `A Warehousing Corporation may, by general or special order in writing,`
  line `delegate to the Secretary or other officer of the Corporation, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act as`
  line `it may deem necessary for the efficient performance of its functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (21026)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Voting rights of shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21026&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `In any meeting of the shareholders of a Warehousing`
  line `Corporation, every member shall have one vote in respect of each share held by him in the`
  line Corporation.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (21027)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Disputes between Central Warehousing Corporation and State Warehousing Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21027&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `If there is any difference of opinion between the Central Warehousing Corporation`
  line `and a State Warehousing Corporation regarding their respective functions and powers under this Act,`
  line `such difference shall be referred to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (21028)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Declaration of fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21028&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every director, auditor, officer or other employee of a`
  line `Warehousing Corporation shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and`
  line `secrecy in the form set out in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (21029)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Indemnity of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21029&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director of a Warehousing Corporation shall be`
  line `indemnified by the Corporation concerned against all losses and expenses incurred in the discharge of`
  line `his duties except such as are caused by his own wilful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A director of a Warehousing Corporation shall not be responsible for any other director or for`
  line `any officer or other employee of the Corporation or for any loss or expense resulting to the`
  line `Corporation by the insufficiency or deficiency of value of, or title to, any property or security`
  line `acquired or taken on behalf of the Corporation in good faith, or by the wrongful act of any person under obligation to the Corporation or by anything done in good faith in the execution of the duties of`
  line `his office or in relation thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (21030)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21030&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, without the consent in writing of a Warehousing Corporation, uses`
  line `the name of that Corporation in any prospectus or advertisement, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under sub-section (1) otherwise than on a`
  line `complaint in writing by an officer authorised in this behalf by the Warehousing Corporation`
  line concerned.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (21031)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Provisions relating to income-tax and super-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21031&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961 (43 of 1961), a Warehousing Corporation shall be deemed to be a company within the meaning`
  line `of that Act and shall be liable to income-tax and super-tax accordingly on its income, profits and`
  line `gains:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of the Central Warehousing Corporation, any sum paid by the Central`
  line `Government under the guarantee given in pursuance of sub-section (1) of section 5 or, in the case of a`
  line `Warehousing Corporation, any sum paid by the Central or a State Government under any guarantee`
  line `given in pursuance of sub-section (4) of section 27 shall not be treated as income, profits and gains of`
  line `a Warehousing Corporation, and any interest on the debentures or bonds issued by that Corporation`
  line `out of such sums shall not be treated as expenditure incurred by it:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of any shareholder or debenture-holder, such portion of a`
  line `dividend or interest as has been paid out of any such sum advanced by the Central Government shall`
  line `be deemed to be his income from interest on securities declared to be income-tax-free within the`
  line `meaning of section 86 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (21032)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Winding up of Warehousing Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21032&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No provision of law relating to the winding`
  line `up of companies or corporations shall apply to a Warehousing Corporation and any such Corporation`
  line `shall not be placed in liquidation save by order of the appropriate Government and in such manner as`
  line `it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (21033)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21033&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the additional functions which a Warehousing Corporation may perform;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of nomination and election of the directors of the Central Warehousing`
  line `Corporation and the period within which such directors shall be nominated or elected;`
  line
  line `(c) the term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, and the`
  line `remuneration payable to, the directors of a Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of choosing directors on the Executive Committee of a Warehousing`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(e) the authorised capital of a State Warehousing Corporation ^1[within the maximum limit`
  line `specified by or under sub-section (1) of section 19];`
  line
  line `(f) the form of the annual statement of accounts and the balance sheet to be prepared by a`
  line `Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(g) the deposit of moneys of a Warehousing Corporation in a scheduled bank or a cooperative`
  line bank;
  line
  line `(h) the manner of issuing shares of a Warehousing Corporation, the calls to be made in`
  line `respect thereof, and all other matters incidental to the issue of shares;`
  line
  line `^2[(i) the form and manner in which returns, statistics, accounts and other information are to`
  line `be furnished, under section 31A, by a Warehousing Corporation;]`
  line
  line `^3[(j)] any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and ^4[if before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session] or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so however that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity`
  line `of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 10, for "within the limit specified in sub-section (1) of section 19" (w.e.f. 24-3- 1976).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 42 of 1976, s. 10 (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (i) re-lettered as clause (j) thereof by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid" (w.e.f. 24-3-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (21034)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power of Warehousing Corporations to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21034&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Warehousing`
  line `Corporation may, with the previous sanction of the appropriate Government, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to`
  line `provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purposes of giving effect`
  line `to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations`
  line `may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions of service of, and the remuneration payable to, the officers and other`
  line `employees of a Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which, and the conditions subject to which, shares of the Central`
  line `Warehousing Corporation may be transferred;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which meetings of a Warehousing Corporation and the Executive`
  line `Committee thereof shall be convened, the fees for attending such meetings and the procedure to`
  line `be followed thereat;`
  line
  line `(d) the duties and conduct of officers and employees of a Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(e) the powers and duties which may be entrusted or delegated to the managing director of a`
  line `Warehousing Corporation;`
  line
  line `(f) generally, the efficient conduct of the affairs of a Warehousing Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, rescind any`
  line `regulation which it has sanctioned and thereupon the regulation shall cease to have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (21035)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370&sectionId=21035&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_28_00005_196258_1517807321370
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from the date on which the Central Warehousing`
  line `Corporation is established under section 3, the Agricultural Produce (Development and Warehousing)`
  line `Corporations Act, 1956 (28 of 1956), in so far as it has not been repealed by the National`
  line `Co-operative Development Corporation Act, 1962 (26 of 1962), shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) the shares allotted and the share certificates issued by the Central Warehousing`
  line `Corporation established under the repealed Act (hereinafter referred to as the said Corporation)`
  line `shall be deemed to have been allotted and issued by the Corporation established under section 3 of this Act as if this Act had been in force on the day on which the shares were allotted and the`
  line `share certificates were issued;`
  line
  line `(b) every shareholder of the said Corporation shall become the holder of as many shares in`
  line `the Corporation established under section 3 of this Act as are equivalent in number and value to`
  line `the shares held by him in the said Corporation;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys and other securities belonging to the National Warehousing Development Fund`
  line `which, immediately before the said date, was maintained by the said Corporation shall stand`
  line `transferred to and be maintained by the Corporation established under section 3 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) anything done or any action taken (including any appointment, nomination, delegation,`
  line `rule or regulation made) under the repealed Act shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) every share held by the said Corporation in a State Warehousing Corporation under the`
  line `repealed Act shall be deemed to be a share held by the Corporation established under section 3 of`
  line `this Act in the corresponding State Warehousing Corporation deemed to be established under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(f) all rights, liabilities and obligations of the said Corporation, whether arising out of any`
  line `contract or otherwise, shall be the rights, liabilities and obligations respectively of the Corporation`
  line `established under section 3 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) a State Warehousing Corporation established for a State under the repealed Act shall be`
  line `deemed to be the State Warehousing Corporation established for that State under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
